      "comment": "REBEL YELL (2) is a two-year-old filly by Imperador out of Maleficent stepping out on debut for the Carlos Daniel Etchechoury stable. Should measure up. Keep a close eye on betting. DEEP HEART (1) is a two-year-old filly at the races for the first time. From an elite family that includes black type success, being by Dabster from Hareer. Comes out of the the strong juvenile stable of Juan Franco Saldivia. Should get all the favours from this good gate and any market lead would add to the confidence. MOON SOLD (7) is a two-year-old filly at the races for the first time. From a G1 winning family, being by Made You Look from Moon Sale. Looks set to make a positive start to her career despite a tricky barrier. THE GREAT LOVE (8) is a beautifully bred two-year-old filly lining up for the first time. By The Great Day from Embracing Love who has produced a winner at the elite level. Sure to be well-educated, being from the Lucas Francisco Gaitan yard. Worth considering.",
